{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17412780","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17412780"},"attributes":{"position":11,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1334"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17494460","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17494460"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T07:41:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T07:41:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1334"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261074"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:38:50+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T07:40:20+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":19,"questionsAnswered":7,"marksTotal":19,"marksAttainable":7,"marksAttempted":7,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T07:39:59+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.14,"questionsCorrect":1,"marksCorrect":1},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"1334","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1334"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.34,0.39,0.03,0.09,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1334"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"33647"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1334","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1334"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1334"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18985"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"709"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5691"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1979"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1983"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"33647","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/33647"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old man is brought to hospital after collapsing at home. His Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) score is 6 and a CT scan shows a massive haemorrhage, occupying much of his right cerebral hemisphere. After 10 days of supportive therapy including nasogastric feeding, he remains unconscious with no change in the GCS. The patient does not have any advanced medical directive and has not appointed any power of guardianship.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHis wife indicates that her husband would not have wished to end up in a nursing home and requests all active support to be withdrawn. His estranged son insists on continuing active support.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next action?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Accede to the wife\u0027s wishes as she is next of kin","Convene a family meeting","Seek advice from the patient\u0027s general practitioner","Involve the Chairman of the hospital\u0027s Ethics Committee","Contact the Guardianship Board"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EUnfortunately events like this happen all too frequently in medical practice. One of the first duties of the medical staff looking after any patient with a life-threatening condition is to clarify if there is any documentation (Advanced Care Directives or 7-step pathways) from the patient regarding their wishes should such an event befall them. If not - and the patient is still autonomous and able to give undergo informed consent - then the individual should be asked to state their wishes for their care should things take a turn for the worse.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThings become more difficult when the patient cannot give clear direction and family member disagree amongst themselves as to what they would like done, with no clear documentation of advanced care directives or power of guardianship. Whilst any decision-making remains the ultimate responsibility of the medical team caring for the patient, every effort must be made to try and get unanimity of opinion from family members - and from those looking after the patient. This usually is done in the form of a \u003Cstrong\u003Efamily meeting\u003C/strong\u003E to discuss goals of care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf agreement cannot be reached, the decision made by the medical team must be evaluated as closest to what they believe the patient themselves would have wanted; thus, the wife\u0027s opinion has more weight than the estranged son in this case.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["All patients - or potential patients - should be encouraged to create an Advanced Care Directive."],"references":["Lichtenthal WG, Kissane DW. The management of family conflict in palliative care. Prog Palliat Care. 2008 Feb 1;16(1):39-45. doi: 10.1179/096992608x296914. PMID: 24027358; PMCID: PMC3767457."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18985"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1334"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18985","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/18985"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-03-15T20:27:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2023-03-15T20:27:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"ty